If other win+key related shortcuts aren't working either, it doesn't sound like classic shell is the cause. <br />Does win+e open file explorer? <br /><br />If nothing with the windows key works, it's possible the key was remapped:<br /><a href="http://lifehacker.com/5883003/the-best-key-remapper-for-windows" class="postlink">http://www.majorgeeks.com/files/details/keytweak.html</a> This tool would allow you map it back to where it belongs if that is the case<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Mon Oct 10, 2016 6:06 am</p><hr />
